Even the last blocks of the authors fall when the final scene arrives, but despite all the power and charm, the film still feels a bit made for a children’s audience.
The film can be considered moderate.
When watching Johnny English films, I’ve come to the same conclusion before: why is the British film industry not able to give Rowan Atkinson a role that would do justice to his talent?
